---
/**
 * rest-api/0003 · Figure 1 — "why the most-worth-retrying request is the most
 * dangerous" (the retry → duplicate-order hero).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0003-idempotency-in-practice.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page defines its arrow markers (#arw, #arwR, …) ONCE in a global
 * hidden <svg> in <body>; that shared SVG does not travel with an extracted
 * figure, so the markers this figure references (#arw, #arwR) are inlined here in
 * a local <defs> so the figure renders self-contained. Marker fills/ids are kept
 * byte-for-byte to match the source DOM.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 660 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Retry danger: POST creates an order, the response is lost, the client retries, a duplicate order is created"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="330"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">WHY THE MOST-WORTH-RETRYING REQUEST IS THE MOST DANGEROUS</text
            >
            <rect x="8" y="42" width="150" height="54" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="83" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700"
                >① POST /orders</text
            >
            <text x="83" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">client sends</text
            >
            <rect x="174" y="42" width="150" height="54" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="249"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">② order created ✓</text
            >
            <text x="249" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >server commits</text
            >
            <rect
                x="340"
                y="42"
                width="150"
                height="54"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
            <text
                x="415"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">③ 201 lost ✗</text
            >
            <text x="415" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >timeout / drop</text
            >
            <rect x="506" y="42" width="146" height="54" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="579"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">④ retry → dupe 💥</text
            >
            <text x="579" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >2 orders · 2 charges</text
            >
            <line x1="158" y1="69" x2="174" y2="69" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="324" y1="69" x2="340" y2="69" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="490" y1="69" x2="506" y2="69" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
            <text x="330" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#7a1f12"
                >The client can't tell "succeeded but reply lost" from "failed" — so it does the
                only sane thing: it retries.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Idempotency makes <strong>at-least-once delivery safe</strong>: a repeated request has the
        same effect on state as a single one.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
